20 GitHub Goldmine Repositories Every Developer Should Know
1. developer-roadmap
https://github.com/kamranahmedse/developer-roadmap → Clear, role‑based roadmaps showing what to learn next for different tech careers.


2. coding-interview-university
https://github.com/jwasham/coding-interview-university → Complete CS + interview prep curriculum covering DSA, OS, DBMS, networking.


3. system-design-primer
https://github.com/donnemartin/system-design-primer → Most popular repo for learning scalability, databases, caching, and system design interviews.


4. awesome-system-design-resources
https://github.com/ashishps1/awesome-system-design-resources → Curated list of the best blogs, videos, and case studies on system design.


5. StriversA2ZDSACourse
https://github.com/striver79/StriversA2ZDSACourse → Structured DSA learning path focused on patterns and interview preparation.


6. leetcode-patterns
https://github.com/seanprashad/leetcode-patterns → Groups LeetCode problems by patterns to build problem‑solving intuition.


7. build-your-own-x
https://github.com/codecrafters-io/build-your-own-x → Learn system internals by building tools like databases, Git, Redis, and OS from scratch.


8. the-art-of-command-line
https://github.com/jlevy/the-art-of-command-line → Teaches how to use the terminal effectively and work like a power user.


9. awesome-scalability
https://github.com/binhnguyennus/awesome-scalability → Deep resources on scaling systems, handling traffic, and avoiding bottlenecks.


10. architecture-of-open-source-applications
https://github.com/aosabook/500lines → Explains how real open‑source systems are architected and designed internally.


11. engineering-blogs
https://github.com/kilimchoi/engineering-blogs → Aggregates engineering blogs from top tech companies like Netflix, Uber, Stripe.


12. design-patterns-for-humans
https://github.com/kamranahmedse/design-patterns-for-humans → Simple explanations of software design patterns with real‑world intuition.


13. backend-developer-roadmap
https://github.com/kamranahmedse/backend-developer-roadmap → Shows everything required to become a production‑ready backend developer.


14. awesome-devops
https://github.com/wmariuss/awesome-devops → Curated DevOps resources covering CI/CD, cloud, containers, and monitoring.


15. kubernetes-the-hard-way
https://github.com/kelseyhightower/kubernetes-the-hard-way → Learn Kubernetes by manually setting it up to understand how it actually works.


16. ossu/computer-science
https://github.com/ossu/computer-science → A full free computer science curriculum using top university resources.


17. free-programming-books
https://github.com/EbookFoundation/free-programming-books → Massive collection of free programming books across languages and domains.


18. awesome
https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome → Entry point to thousands of curated “awesome lists” for almost every tech topic.


19. public-apis
https://github.com/public-apis/public-apis → Huge list of free public APIs for building real‑world projects and portfolios.


20. backend-checklist
https://github.com/fpereiro/backendlore → Practical checklist of things every backend engineer should consider in production systems.
